{"content": "I need to multiply 139 \u00d7 971 in base 11.\n\n**Step 1: Convert 139 (base 11) to base 10**\n- 139\u2081\u2081 = 1\u00d711\u00b2 + 3\u00d711\u00b9 + 9\u00d711\u2070\n- = 1\u00d7121 + 3\u00d711 + 9\u00d71\n- = 121 + 33 + 9\n- = 163\u2081\u2080\n\n**Step 2: Convert 971 (base 11) to base 10**\n- 971\u2081\u2081 = 9\u00d711\u00b2 + 7\u00d711\u00b9 + 1\u00d711\u2070\n- = 9\u00d7121 + 7\u00d711 + 1\u00d71\n- = 1089 + 77 + 1\n- = 1167\u2081\u2080\n\n**Step 3: Multiply in base 10**\n- 163 \u00d7 1167 = 190,221\u2081\u2080\n\n**Step 4: Convert 190,221 (base 10) to base 11**\n- 190,221 \u00f7 11 = 17,292 R 9\n- 17,292 \u00f7 11 = 1,572 R 0\n- 1,572 \u00f7 11 = 142 R 10 (a)\n- 142 \u00f7 11 = 12 R 10 (a)\n- 12 \u00f7 11 = 1 R 1\n- 1 \u00f7 11 = 0 R 1\n\nReading remainders from bottom to top: 11aa09\n\n**Answer: 11aa09**", "model": "anthropic/claude-sonnet-4.5", "prompt_tokens": 363, "completion_tokens": 413}